Signed-off-by: Alberto Bertogli <albertito@gmail.com>

Update the "Automatic compression" entry to reflect the new git gc behaviour

git gc is now automatically run by default, update the paragraph
accordingly.

Signed-off-by: Alberto Bertogli <albertito@gmail.com>

Remove clone -l -s references

-l (--local) is not needed anymore, as it is the default when cloning from
a regular path (as opposed to a URI).

-s is not newbie-friendly and dangerous, as automatic gc can remove
objects referenced in another repository and moving the original clone can
break the new one.

This patch removes both, updating the text accordingly. The clone is fast
enough anyway.

Signed-off-by: Alberto Bertogli <albertito@gmail.com>

Normalize capitalization of commit messages

It is the recommended practise to start the commit messages with a capital
letter, but in the document some were and some were not.

This patch makes capitalices the remaining messages.

Signed-off-by: Alberto Bertogli <albertito@gmail.com>
